metadata.name: Year
metadata.description: Year of creation of the feature model

metadata.name: Reference
metadata.description: Main paper for reference or DOI of the feature model

metadata.name: Tags
metadata.description: Tags or keywords that identify the feature model.

metrics.name: Features
metrics.description: Set of features in the feature model.

metrics.name: Abstract features
metrics.description: Features used to structure the feature model that, however, do not have any impact at implementation level.

metrics.name: Abstract leaf features
metrics.description: Abstract and leaf features.

metrics.name: Abstract compound features
metrics.description: Abstract and compound features.

metrics.name: Concrete features
metrics.description: Features that are mapped to at least one implementation artifact.

metrics.name: Concrete leaf features
metrics.description: Concrete and leaf features.

metrics.name: Concrete compound features
metrics.description: Concrete and compound features.

metrics.name: Compound features
metrics.description: Features that have subfeatures.

metrics.name: Leaf features
metrics.description: Features that have not subfeatures (aka 'primitive features' or 'terminal features').

metrics.name: Root feature
metrics.description: The root of the feature model.

metrics.name: Top features
metrics.description: Features that are first descendants of the root.

metrics.name: Solitary features
metrics.description: Features that are not grouped in a feature group.

metrics.name: Grouped features
metrics.description: Features that occurs in a feature group.

metrics.name: Typed features
metrics.description: Non-Boolean features its selection require to provide a value (e.g., a number, a string,...

metrics.name: Numerical features
metrics.description: Features with a Integer or Real type.

metrics.name: Integer features
metrics.description: Features with a Integer type.

metrics.name: Real features
metrics.description: Features with a Real type.

metrics.name: String features
metrics.description: Features with a String type.

metrics.name: Multi-features
metrics.description: Features with cardinalities (aka 'clonable features')

metrics.name: Tree relationships
metrics.description: Number of relationships (edges) of the feature model.

metrics.name: Mutex groups
metrics.description: Feature groups that require the selection of zero or just one child (i.e., [0..1] cardinality).

metrics.name: Cardinality groups
metrics.description: Feature groups with arbitraty cardinality [a..b] that require the selection of an minimum and a maximum number of children.

metrics.name: Depth of tree
metrics.description: Number of features of the longest path from the root to the leaf features.

metrics.name: Mean depth of tree
metrics.description: Number of features of the mean path from the root to the leaf features.

metrics.name: Branching factor
metrics.description: Average number of children per non-leaf feature (aka 'Ratio of Variability').

metrics.name: Min children per feature
metrics.description: Minimal number of children per non-leaf feature.

metrics.name: Max children per feature
metrics.description: Maximal number of children per feature.

metrics.name: Avg children per feature
metrics.description: Average number of children per feature.

metrics.name: Arithmetic constraints
metrics.description: Constraints with at least one arithmetic operator.

metrics.name: Aggregation constraints
metrics.description: Constraints with at least one aggregation operator.

metrics.name: Features in constraints
metrics.description: Features involved in cross-tree constraints. The ratio to the total number of features is called 'Extra constraint representativeness (ECR)'.

metrics.name: Min features per constraint
metrics.description: The minimal number of features involved per cross-tree constraint.

metrics.name: Max features per constraint
metrics.description: The maximal number of features involved per cross-tree constraint.

metrics.name: Avg features per constraint
metrics.description: The average number of features involved per cross-tree constraint.

metrics.name: Avg constraints per feature
metrics.description: The average number of constraints per feature.

metrics.name: Min constraints per feature
metrics.description: The minimal number of constraints per feature.

metrics.name: Max constraints per feature
metrics.description: The maximal number of constraints per feature.

metrics.name: Attributes
metrics.description: Features attributes in the model (i.e., number of distinct attributes).

metrics.name: Features with attributes
metrics.description: Features that contain some attributes defined in the model.

metrics.name: Min attributes per feature
metrics.description: The minimal number of attributes in a feature.

metrics.name: Max attributes per feature
metrics.description: The maximal number of attributes in a feature.

metrics.name: Avg attributes per feature
metrics.description: Average number of attributes in features.

metrics.name: Avg attributes per feature w. attributes
metrics.description: Average number of attributes in features with attributes.

analysis.name: Satisfiable (valid)
analysis.description: A feature model is satisfiable (valid, not void) if it represents at least one configuration.

analysis.name: Core features
analysis.description: Features that are part of all the configurations (aka 'common features').

analysis.name: False-optional features
analysis.description: Features included in all possible configurations although not being modelled as mandatory. The ratio is based on the total number of features.

analysis.name: Dead features
analysis.description: Features that cannot appear in any configuration.

analysis.name: Variant features
analysis.description: Features that appear only in some configurations (i.e., features that are neither core nor dead).

analysis.name: Unique features
analysis.description: Features that appear in exactly one configuration. The ratio is based on the total number of features.

analysis.name: Pure optional features
analysis.description: Feature with 0.5 (50%) probability of being selected in a valid configuration (i.e., their selection is unconstrained). The ratio is based on the total number of features.

analysis.name: Configurations
analysis.description: Number of configurations represented by the feature model. If <= is shown, the number represents an upper estimation bound.

analysis.name: Total variability
analysis.description: The total variability measures the flexibility of the SPL considering all features.

analysis.name: Partial variability
analysis.description: The partial variability measures the flexibility of the SPL considering only variant features.

analysis.name: Homogeneity
analysis.description: The homogeneity measures how similar are the configurations of the SPL.

analysis.name: Configuration distribution
analysis.description: Number of configurations having a given number of features.

analysis.name: Mean
analysis.description: Mean number of features occurring in configurations.

analysis.name: Standard deviation
analysis.description: Standard deviation of number of features in configurations.

analysis.name: Median
analysis.description: Median number of features in configurations.

analysis.name: Median absolute deviation
analysis.description: Median absolute deviation number of features in configurations.

analysis.name: Mode
analysis.description: Most frequently occurring number of features for a configuration.

analysis.name: Min
analysis.description: Number of features in the smallest configuration.

analysis.name: Max
analysis.description: Number of features in the largest configuration.

analysis.name: Range
analysis.description: Range of number of features in configurations.
